Rescue officials responded to a drowning in progress shortly after 2pm yesterday. CAPE TOWN - The search for a Khayelitsha man presumed to have drowned at Monwabisi beach is still underway. Rescue officials responded to a drowning in progress shortly after 2pm yesterday. Law Enforcement Marine Lifeguards rescued a secondman and treated him for exhaustion. The National Sea Rescue Institute's Craig Lambinon says: Police divers are continuing to search for a 45-year-old Khayelitsha man this afternoon at Monwabisi. It appears he and a friend were swimming when they got into difficulty.